description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Care Co-ordinator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join Scarborough Core Primary Care Network (PCN), working as a Care Co-ordinator across 4 Practices with a total population of 52,000 patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Care Coordinator you will be the key link to the people whose care you are supporting, operating as a go to person to ensure that their care is seamless, they are active decision makers in their own care, and that everyone involved is working together. They will work closely with the GPs, Care Home Managers and other primary care professionals to identify and support care home patients across the PCN, making sure that appropriate support is made available to them, and ensuring that their changing needs are addressed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the role evolves the Care Co-ordinator will undertake direct work with patients and families to support the development of personalised care and support plans. An ethos of promotion of independence, shared decision making, personalisation and partnership-working is integral to this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a dynamic person wishing to build on their current experience and knowledge who can offer us excellent communication, organisational and interpersonal skills. You will need to be flexible and enjoy working in a busy environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a new and developing role that will form part of the PCN multi-disciplinary team (MDT). You will work in partnership with your clinical and non-clinical colleagues, management support and the wider PCN to ensure the role delivers the best possible outcomes for our patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We may close the advert early due to the number of applicants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent position&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;12 month probationary period&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;25 days holiday plus bank holiday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note under GDPR we will keep your personal data for the required time only and it will be disposed of securely.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Types: Full-time, Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary: £21,892 – £23,123/year&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
